Paul Herman, News24The vehicle involved in the accident on the N3 near Tollgate Bridge in Durban. (Supplied: Advanced Life Support) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; One person has been killed and three injured in two separate accidents in Durban.Two vehicles collided on the N3 near the Tollgate Bridge around 03:30 on Saturday morning, killing a man in his twenties, Advanced Life Support spokesperson Ceron Lennox said.Two people were seriously injured, and were treated on the scene.Overturned truckIn a separate incident, a truck overturned around 10:20 on Saturday on the M13, Fields Hill near Pinetown, Durban, Netcare911 spokesperson Chris Botha said.The truck was lying on its side, obstructing the inbound traffic.The driver escaped with minor injuries.The three injured were transported to nearby hospitals. The causes of both accidents were being investigated. The overturned truck on the M13, Fields Hill. (Supplied: Netcare)24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.